This paper is about neural network compression, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The paper specifically focuses on evaluating the efficacy of different compression techniques on basic architectures on the MNIST dataset and its variants. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) since convolutional neural networks are mentioned. Other likely categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) since the paper deals with optimization techniques for neural networks.
